# Axis 4 — callback re-entry

A higher-order function receives a managed closure and re-enters it multiple
times. At the interop boundary this is the "managed callback" case: a host
callback is a terminal adapter over this managed-closure capability (never an
alternate control semantics). Intra-lane baseline here.

```scalascript
def apply3(f: Int => Int, x: Int): Int = f(f(f(x)))
println(apply3(n => n * 2, 1))
```
